<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C48F05759434FCC3" bold="true" box="[151,287,775,801]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C53D057597A5FCC0" authority="Wang &amp; Li, 2021" authorityName="Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2021" box="[293,654,775,802]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wandae">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C53D057594E3FCC3" box="[293,456,775,801]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Rhene wandae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB9FFC7C5D6057A97A5FCC0" author="Wang, C. &amp; Li, S. Q." box="[462,654,775,802]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" pagination="123 - 155" refId="ref8712" refString="Wang, C. &amp; Li, S. Q. (2021) On ten species of jumping spiders from Xishuangbanna, China (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys, 1062, 123 - 155. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 1062.72531" type="journal article" year="2021">Wang &amp; Li, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on the 
<typeStatus id="182E8838FFB9FFC7C7D005759101FCC3" box="[968,1066,775,801]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">holotype</typeStatus>
male and the 
<typeStatus id="182E8838FFB9FFC7C0DB057A9008FCC0" box="[1219,1315,776,802]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">paratype</typeStatus>
male from Xishuangbanna, 
<collectingRegion id="0551F878FFB9FFC7C54D055E9485FCA4" box="[341,430,812,838]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="BF82760AFFB9FFC7C5A305599729FCA7" box="[443,514,811,837]" name="China" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">China</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C61705599680FCA4" authority="Logunov, 2021" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2021" box="[527,939,811,838]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhenefictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tropicus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C617055997DDFCA7" box="[527,758,811,837]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Rhenefictus tropicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB9FFC7C6E7055E9680FCA4" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[767,939,812,838]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" pagination="1021 - 1055" refId="ref7624" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2021) Jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae) of the Na Hang Nature Reserve, Tuyen Quang Province, Vietnam. Arachnology, 18 (9), 1021 - 1055. https: // doi. org / 10.13156 / arac. 2021.18.9.1021" type="journal article" year="2021">Logunov, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on the 
<typeStatus id="182E8838FFB9FFC7C0E205599077FCA7" box="[1274,1372,811,837]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">holotype</typeStatus>
male from the 
<collectingRegion id="0551F878FFB9FFC7C4E3052294D6FC8B" box="[251,509,847,874]" country="Vietnam" name="Tuyen Quang" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Tuyen Quang Province</collectingRegion>
in northern 
<collectingCountry id="BF82760AFFB9FFC7C69A053D97CEFC8B" box="[642,741,847,873]" name="Vietnam" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
. While comparing the illustrations of both species, it is evident that they depict the same species. The unique male palp with the long whip-like, coiled embolus lacking a terminal apophysis (cf. figs 
<quantity id="006D9B7FFFB9FFC7C57105E594C3FC53" box="[361,488,919,945]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1242" metricValueMax="3.2004" metricValueMin="3.048" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" unit="in" value="123.0" valueMax="126.0" valueMin="120.0">120–126 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB9FFC7C5F505EA9788FC50" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[493,675,920,946]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" pagination="1021 - 1055" refId="ref7624" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2021) Jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae) of the Na Hang Nature Reserve, Tuyen Quang Province, Vietnam. Arachnology, 18 (9), 1021 - 1055. https: // doi. org / 10.13156 / arac. 2021.18.9.1021" type="journal article" year="2021">Logunov (2021)</bibRefCitation>
with figs 16A–C, 17A–D in 
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB9FFC7C7FB05EA9193FC50" author="Wang, C. &amp; Li, S. Q." box="[995,1208,919,946]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" pagination="123 - 155" refId="ref8712" refString="Wang, C. &amp; Li, S. Q. (2021) On ten species of jumping spiders from Xishuangbanna, China (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys, 1062, 123 - 155. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 1062.72531" type="journal article" year="2021">Wang &amp; Li (2021))</bibRefCitation>
is a diagnostic characteristic of the newly erected genus 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C63705C99649FC34" authority="Logunov, 2021" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2021" box="[559,866,955,982]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhenefictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C63705C99799FC37" box="[559,690,955,981]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Rhenefictus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB9FFC7C6AF05CE9649FC34" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[695,866,956,982]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" pagination="1021 - 1055" refId="ref7624" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2021) Jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae) of the Na Hang Nature Reserve, Tuyen Quang Province, Vietnam. Arachnology, 18 (9), 1021 - 1055. https: // doi. org / 10.13156 / arac. 2021.18.9.1021" type="journal article" year="2021">Logunov, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Despite both descriptions being published in 2021, the paper by Wang &amp; Li appeared in October, whereas that of Logunov in November. Therefore, the name 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C14E05AD95C5FBFF" authorityName="Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wandae">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C14E05AD95C5FBFF" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Rhene wandae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a priority over 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C5C802769629FBFC" authority="Logunov, 2021" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2021" box="[464,770,1028,1054]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhenefictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tropicus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C5C802769767FBFF" box="[464,588,1028,1053]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">R. tropicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB9FFC7C64C02769629FBFC" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[596,770,1028,1054]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" pagination="1021 - 1055" refId="ref7624" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2021) Jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae) of the Na Hang Nature Reserve, Tuyen Quang Province, Vietnam. Arachnology, 18 (9), 1021 - 1055. https: // doi. org / 10.13156 / arac. 2021.18.9.1021" type="journal article" year="2021">Logunov, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and the latter is to be considered a junior synonym of the former. Yet, the validity of the newly erected, monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C77B025596CDFBA3" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2021" box="[867,998,1063,1089]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhenefictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C77B025596CDFBA3" box="[867,998,1063,1089]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Rhenefictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains unquestioned, and thus 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C14E025595C5FB87" authorityName="Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wandae">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C14E025595C5FB87" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Rhene wandae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is to be transferred to this genus: 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C6470239913DFB84" authority="(Wang &amp; Li, 2021)" authorityName="Caleb &amp; Sanap &amp; Tripathi &amp; Sampathkumar &amp; Dharmaraj &amp; Packiam" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Wang &amp; Li" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[607,1046,1099,1126]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhenefictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wandae" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C64702399615FB87" box="[607,830,1099,1125]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Rhenefictus wandae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB9FFC7C753023E9126FB84" author="Wang, C. &amp; Li, S. Q." box="[843,1037,1099,1126]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" pagination="123 - 155" refId="ref8712" refString="Wang, C. &amp; Li, S. Q. (2021) On ten species of jumping spiders from Xishuangbanna, China (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys, 1062, 123 - 155. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 1062.72531" type="journal article" year="2021">Wang &amp; Li, 2021</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="EED257F3FFB9FFC7C00302399150FB84" box="[1051,1147,1099,1126]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" rank="species">comb. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Finally, despite the newly established synonymy and based on Article 67.1.2 of the ICZN, 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C76F021D903BFB68" authority="Logunov, 2021" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2021" box="[887,1296,1135,1162]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhenefictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tropicus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C76F021D9176FB6B" box="[887,1117,1135,1161]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Rhenefictus tropicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB9FFC7C07D0202903BFB68" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[1125,1296,1136,1162]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" pagination="1021 - 1055" refId="ref7624" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2021) Jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae) of the Na Hang Nature Reserve, Tuyen Quang Province, Vietnam. Arachnology, 18 (9), 1021 - 1055. https: // doi. org / 10.13156 / arac. 2021.18.9.1021" type="journal article" year="2021">Logunov, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
remains the type species of 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C55D02E194E3FB4F" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2021" box="[325,456,1171,1197]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhenefictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C55D02E194E3FB4F" box="[325,456,1171,1197]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Rhenefictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is now regarded as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C76402E191C6FB4C" authority="Wang &amp; Li, 2021" authorityName="Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2021" box="[892,1261,1171,1198]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wandae">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C76402E1910BFB4F" box="[892,1056,1171,1197]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Rhene wandae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB9FFC7C03F02E691C6FB4C" author="Wang, C. &amp; Li, S. Q." box="[1063,1261,1171,1198]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" pagination="123 - 155" refId="ref8712" refString="Wang, C. &amp; Li, S. Q. (2021) On ten species of jumping spiders from Xishuangbanna, China (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys, 1062, 123 - 155. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 1062.72531" type="journal article" year="2021">Wang &amp; Li, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
